.TH "ATOMDNS" 1 "February 2026" "atomdns" "atomdns authors"

.SH "NAME"
.PP
\fIatomdns\fP \- DNS nameserver that runs handlers

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.PP
\fIatomdns\fP \fB[\-C|\-H|\-V]\fP [CONFFILE]

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
atomdns is a DNS server that chains handlers. Each handler handles a DNS feature, like serve zone files,
transfering those to secondaries or just exporting metrics. There are many handlers, each described in their
respective manual page.

.PP
The server atomdns can be reloaded by sending it the HUP signal, this reloads the handlers only, and does
\fInot\fP restart any of the servers, so changes to server addresses and limits (see atomdns\-global(7)) will not
be applied through reloads. For those kind of changes the server needs to be restarted. Modifiying origins or
handlers are picked up.

.PP
The \fIglobal\fP handler describes the options that are also used in starting the server, see atomdns\-global(7)
for more information. Normally you need a \fBCONFFILE\fP (atomdns\-conffile(5)) like this, to listen on all
interfaces on port 53:

.PP
.RS

.nf
{
    dns {
        addr [::]:53
    }
}

.fi
.RE

.PP
When atomdns starts it emits a bunch of logs telling what zones are loaded and routines are started, when all
succesful you are greeted with a banner (unless \fB\fCquiet\fR is true see atomdns\-global(7)).

.PP
.RS

.nf
  ┏━┓  ╺┳╸  ┏━┓  ┏┳┓
  ┣━┫   ┃   ┃ ┃  ┃┃┃  DNS
  ╹ ╹   ╹   ┗━┛  ╹ ╹ v024 (0.5.15)
  High performance and flexible DNS server
  https://atomdns.miek.nl
\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\\o/\_\_\_\_\_\_\_

.fi
.RE

.PP
There is optional positional argument, the \fBCONFFILE\fP to configure atomdns. If not given atomdns will use
a builtin Conffile:

.PP
.RS

.nf
{
  dns {
      addr [::]1053
  }
}

example.org {
  log
  whoami
}

.fi
.RE

.PP
The following options are available:

.TP
\fB\-C\fP
check the configuration, report any erors and exit with status 1 or if everything is OK exit with status
code 0.
.TP
\fB\-H\fP
list all handlers and quit.
.TP
\fB\-V\fP
Show version and quit.


.SH "HANDLERS"
.PP
The following handlers are available:

.IP \(bu 4
\fIacl\fP \- enforces access control policies. See atomdns\-acl(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIany\fP \- give a minimal response to ANY queries. See atomdns\-any(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIas112\fP \- an AS112 black hole server. See atomdns\-as112(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIchaos\fP \- respond to TXT queries in the CH class. See atomdns\-chaos(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIcookie\fP \- adds an DNS cookie of this server to each reply. See atomdns\-cookie(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIdbfile\fP \- serve zone data from an RFC 1035\-style file. See atomdns\-dbfile(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIdbhosts\fP \- serve data from \fB\fC/etc/hosts\fR. See atomdns\-dbhost(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIdbsqilte\fP \- serve zone data from a SQLite database. See atomdns\-dbsqlite(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIdrunk\fP \- test client behavior. See atomdns\-drunk(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIecs\fP \- add EDNS client subnet to the context. See atomdns\-ecs(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIgeoip\fP \- add geographical location data. See atomdns\-geoip(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIglobal\fP \- hold global server properties. See atomdns\-global(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIid\fP \- add unique ID to the context. See atomdns\-id(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIimport\fP \- includes files or references snippets from a Conffile. See atomdns\-import(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIkill\fP \- stop atomdns after a duration. See atomdns\-kill(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIlog\fP \- log queries. See atomdns\-log(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fImetrics\fP \- enable prometheus
\[la]https://prometheus.io/\[ra] metrics. See atomdns\-metrics(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fInsid\fP \- adds an identifier of this server to each reply. See atomdns\-nsid(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIrefuse\fP \- refuse queries. See atomdns\-refuse(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIsign\fP \- add DNSSEC records to zone files. See atomdns\-sign(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fItemplate\fP \- use Go templates to reply. See atomdns\-template(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIurl\fP \- serve zone data from an URL. See atomdns\-url(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIwhoami\fP \- return your resolver's local IP address, port and transport. See atomdns\-whoami(7).
.IP \(bu 4
\fIyes\fP \- always respond to positively to queries. See atomdns\-yes(7).


